-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/ubs-hires-morgan-stanley-bankers-for-asia-wealth-document-shows.html
UBS AG,  Switzerland â€™s largest bank,
hired ex- Morgan Stanley (MS)  bankers Peter Tung and Harry Pang for
its wealth management unit in the Asia-Pacific region, according
to an internal memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  Tung, who was a managing director at New York-based Morgan
Stanley, will join in September as head of the ultra-high net
worth business for Greater China, Kathryn Shih, chief executive
officer of the wealth management division in the region, said in
the memo to employees today. Singapore-based spokeswoman Rachel Lin confirmed the contents of the document.  Pang, whose appointment is also effective from September,
will be managing director and one of the ultra-high net worth
country team heads for the  China  international business,
according to the document. The Zurich-based bank has hired more
than 200 people for its wealth management unit across Asia
Pacific since the beginning of the year, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
